You'll be so much happier without the mess.
If your life is a mess clean it up.
It doesnâ€™t matter where you start what matters is that you FINISH what you start.
Letting it pile up will make your life worse than it has to be. So, itâ€™s best to just clean it up. No-one wants a messy house or life
Or you can pick one thing in your life to work on first and slowly move to another thing and another until your life isn't messy anymore
Like the messy house person. You can let the mess in your life overwhelm you, and just let it sit there and slowly pile up and uP and UP
Well, a messy life, messed up life is like a messy house. You might not know where you should start because you have so much to do.
However most people pick a room to start in and then they go to another room and another room until they clean up the whole house.
Well,  when some people have a messy house they decide not to start at all because it's too much work,and they let the mess just pile up lol
Well, when you first look at the messy house youâ€™re like where do I start and you stand there or walk around trying to decide where to start
Have you ever had a messy house where every room in the house needed to be cleaned or reorganized?...Well...
I'd rather say "I tried' than "What If"
If you don't know where to start find someone that has reached your goal or dream and use them as a guide and inspiration. Do what they did.
If you don't know where to start remember that you have to start somewhere to get somewhere and doing NOTHING will get you nowhere.

Happy people find a way to live with their problems, and miserable people let their problems stop them from living.
Realize that you're not always going to have someone that believes in you or your dreams.  So, you have to believe in yourself.
Don't let a few flaws or problems stop you from accomplishing something great. Those things won't stop you unless you let them stop you.
While a miserable person is sitting around focusing on 1 thing they can't fix. A happy person is out there fixing 100 things they can fix.
A wise person focuses on the 100 things in their life that they can fix instead of the 1 thing in their life that they can't fix.
Sure it might be stressing you out, but if you can't fix it there's no point in focusing on it. Get busy fixing something that CAN be fixed.
Who will get more things done that day? Who will be proud of themselves at the end of the day?
If 'A' spends their whole day fixing things they CAN change and 'B' spends their whole day stressing things they can't change.......cont
Focus on the things you can't change and get NOTHING done or focus on the things you can change and get SOMETHING done.
However, a person that spends their whole day focusing on things in their life that they CAN change will get a lot of things done.
A person that spends their whole day focusing on things in their life that they CAN'T change won't get anything done.
Don't spend all of your time trying to find love. Love yourself and do what makes you happy and love will find you.
Fight for yourself, your family, your future, your goals, your life and your dreams. FIGHT for every freaking thing that will make you happy
You don't have to chase a man that loves you because he'll already want to be in your life.
Don't chase after a man, if he wanted to be caught he would be walking beside you NOT running away from you.
If they want to watch you and judge you give them something to watch. Let your enemies watch you chase your goals and dreams.
